raw_data.title: CAD Technician
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: One year practical CAD experience and the ability to perform CAD functions for technical projects. Functional Experience: Works closely with design originators, preparing CAD drawings and graphs of original designs, and technical presentations that require a high degree of precision. Minimum Education: High School or technical/vocational school diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Clerk
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: One year performing routine work in support of projects.  Ability to perform support functions under routine supervision. Functional Responsibility: Reproduction of documents, filing, preparation of shipments, data gathering, operation of office computer, general logistic support, etc. Minimum Education: High School diploma or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Computer Programmer/Analyst
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Two years analyst experience related to scientific programming skills with digital computer systems, information systems, data management and/or configuration control applications.  Functional Responsibility: Performs analyses, software design and specification and work statement preparation in support of systems design. Minimum Education:  Associate’s Degree, High School diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Design Engineer
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Four years experience in analysis and/or design of mechanical, electrical, or electronic systems.     Functional Responsibility: Performs a variety of engineering tasks, either independently or under limited supervision. Analyzes configurations and develops feasibility studies and provides recommendations for updating systems to meet modern technologies.  Minimum Education: Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering or Information Technology related field, or four years of college level education, training, and/or technical experience that furnished a thorough knowledge in the specialized area of responsibility.

raw_data.title: Designer
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Two years technical experience in developing engineering drawings, procedures and techniques related to technical systems, and engineering investigations for use in drawings, reports, and test documents. Functional Responsibility: Performs advanced design tasks and guides users in formulating requirements and alternative approaches; mathematical calculations using generally accepted procedures, and basic engineering principles. Minimum Education: High School diploma or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Electrician
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  Two years technical experience in electrical/ cabling systems.  Ability to plan, coordinate, and execute electrical systems integration/installation. Functional Responsibility: Oversees electrical/ cabling systems projects. Minimum Education: High School or vocational school diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Engineer
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Four years technical experience in engineering analysis, design, installation, operation, maintenance, repair, or testing tasks.  Requires competence in engineering techniques, concepts and methods; also requires knowledge of available hardware, software, structure and management practices. Functional Responsibility: Under general supervision, executes systems engineering within a project. Prepares specifications and designs, subsystems and incorporates solutions.      Minimum Education: Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering or Information Technology related field, or Associate’s Degree in a related field and two years technical experience, or four years experience without a degree.

raw_data.title: Engineering Analyst
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Two years technical experience in design, project management and field services within the engineering field ( e.g., Marine, Mechanical, Electrical, Electronics, etc.); system planning, performance management, capacity planning, testing and validation, benchmarking, information engineering.  Ability to define and execute systems engineering and analysis activities within a project.     Functional Responsibility: Guides users in establishing requirements, advises alternative approaches, conducts feasibility studies and analyses. Minimum Education: Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering or Information Technology field, or Associate’s degree in a related field and two years technical experience, or four years engineering experience without a degree.

raw_data.title: Engineer Technician
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  Two years technical experience in mechanical, electrical, or electronics systems.  Familiarity in the preparation of original technical documentation involving the operation, maintenance, and repair of mechanical, electrical, or electronic equipment or systems. Functional Responsibility:  Applies technical knowledge to solve engineering problems.  Prepares engineering change documentation, integration/installation plans, and system testing plans. Minimum Education:  High School diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Equipment Mechanic
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Four years experience and superior technical knowledge directly related to the integration, installation, testing, maintenance, repair and support of mechanical, electrical, or electronic equipment, components, systems, or related structural components.  Possess knowledge and ability to apply basic principles of mathematics, physics, and general science.  Ability to apply and interpret technical manuals, blueprints, sketches, and specifications. Functional Responsibility: Performs all functions related to integration, installation, testing, maintenance and repair of mechanical, electrical, or electronic equipment, components, systems, and related structural components. Minimum Education: High School or vocational school diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Foreman
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Four years in a technical field; ability to read and interpret blueprints, technical manuals and other technical data and sequencing work effectively.  Experience in quality assurance procedures, testing, troubleshooting, and inspecting installed systems equipment and systems.  Ability to direct assigned technicians and craftsmen in the performance of work assignments. Functional Responsibility: Leads assigned technicians and craftsmen in the performance of contract tasks.  Schedules tasks, monitors quality, inspects completed work, and prepares required reports.  Minimum Education:  High School or vocational school diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Industrial Specialist
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  Eight years work experience involving management of industrial projects or related activities. Functional Responsibility:  Planning and estimating of cost and manpower requirements for industrial projects; progressing, scheduling and controlling industrial projects; planning of industrial production, including development of management information cost-accounting and/or statistical control systems. Minimum Education:  Bachelor’s Degree or four years of college level education, training, and/or technical experience that furnished a thorough knowledge in the specialized area of responsibility.

raw_data.title: Inventory Specialist
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Two years experience in processing material receipts; maintenance of an on-going inventory control system; replenishment of stocks; receiving shipping documentation; preparing required reports. Functional Responsibility: Coordination of material receipts, inventory control, outgoing shipments, and records management under minimal supervision. Distribution of materials in accordance with instructions. Minimum Education: High School diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Logistician
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Four years logistical experience in material and Integrated Logistics Support (ILS) programs.  Knowledgeable in the identification of material and ILS requirements, Bid Specifications, application of logistics and procurement systems, and procedures for requisitioning and purchasing program materials and equipment and long lead materials.   Functional Responsibility:  Identifies ILS requirements and coordinates material procurement. Prepares Bid Specifications and reviews specifications for material and equipment. Minimum Education: High School diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Maintenance Technician
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: One year general technical experience related to the integration, installation, testing, maintenance, repair and support of mechanical, electronic, or electrical equipment, components, systems, and related structural components. Must be familiar with and competent in the use of tools of the technical field. Ability to read blueprints, sketches, and specifications and follow directions.     Functional Responsibility:  Performs functions in support of equipment and system integration and installation, and assists technical personnel in the performance of their duties. Minimum Education: High School or vocational school diploma, or equivalent

raw_data.title: Planner/Estimator
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Two years technical experience in preparing cost and time estimates (time, labor, and material) for mechanical, electrical, or electronic systems.  Knowledgeable in production/planning procedures, material requirements, technical instructions, and preparation of contract specifications and estimates. Functional Responsibility: Prepares material, cost and time estimates for contract requirements, and assists in production planning and procedures. Minimum Education: High School diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Six years technical experience in management and oversight of technical programs; competence in reviewing contractual requirements for compliance; liaison with customers; ability to complete programs on time, within budget, and in accordance with customer specifications.   Functional Responsibility: Management of technical programs; identifies problems and develops solutions. Provides reports and maintains close liaison with the customer. Minimum Education:  Bachelor’s Degree or four years of college level education, training, and/or technical experience that furnished a thorough knowledge in the specialized area of responsibility.

raw_data.title: Project Coordinator
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Two years technical experience in management and coordination of technical system programs and projects.   Functional Responsibility: Ensures that project requirements are coordinated and that program objectives are met. Minimum Education: High School diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Four years technical experience in management and oversight of technical projects.  Understanding of contracts, standards, quality and productivity. Functional Responsibility: Provides business, technical, and personnel management for individual projects.  Minimum Education: Bachelor’s or Associate’s Degree in a related field and two years technical experience or four years experience without a degree.

raw_data.title: Purchasing Agent
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Two years practical experience in procurement, ordering procedures, and discounts; knowledge of suppliers and material resources. Functional Responsibility:  Performs procurement of supplies and materials to meet program requirements.  Works with Program Managers and project supervisors to coordinate material purchases and delivery requirements.    Minimum Education:  High School diploma or equivalent.

raw_data.title: QA Specialist
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Four years technical experience which has provided a practical knowledge of quality assurance programs, quality control inspection systems, and a detailed knowledge of shop procedures, processes, methods and techniques.  Functional Responsibility: Coordinates quality assurance activities such as test plans, criteria and procedures, assembly of test data results, and conducting, evaluating and verifying test results for systems monitored. Minimum Education: High School diploma or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Senior CAD Technician
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: One year technical experience in CAD drawing involving complex technical systems. Functional Experience: Works closely with design originators, preparing CAD drawings and graphs of complex/original designs, and technical presentations which require a high degree of precision. Minimum Education: High School or technical/vocational school diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Senior Designer
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Four years technical experience in developing advanced engineering drawings, procedures and techniques related to technical systems or engineering investigations for use in drawings, reports, and test documents. Functional Responsibility: Performs advanced design tasks and guides users in formulating requirements and alternative approaches; mathematical calculations using generally accepted procedures, and basic engineering principles. Minimum Education: High School diploma or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Senior Electrician
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  Four years advanced technical experience in electrical/electronic and cabling systems.  Ability to plan, coordinate, and execute electrical systems integration/ installation. Functional Responsibility: Oversees electrical/electronic/cabling systems projects. Minimum Education:  High School or vocational school diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Senior Engineer Technician
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Four years technical experience in mechanical, electrical, or electronics systems.  Requires competence in the preparation of original technical documentation involving the operation, maintenance, and repair of mechanical, electrical, or electronic equipment and systems.  Functional Responsibility: Applies advanced technical knowledge to solve complex problems.  Prepares engineering change documentation, integration/installation plans, and system testing plans.   Minimum Education: High School diploma, or equivalent

raw_data.title: Supervisor
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Six years experience working in a trade or technical field, with 3 of these years comprising supervisory experience.  Functional Responsibility: Directs assigned technicians and craftsmen in the accomplishment of integration, installation, and/or removal of alterations within budget and on schedule. Reviews work specifications, develops project material and equipment lists, prioritizes work tasks and resolves conflicting demands, ensures work orders are completed correctly and efficiently. Minimum Education: High School or vocational school diploma, or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Systems Analyst
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Two years systems experience in Statistical and/or Engineering Systems Analysis; devising and preparation of designs and developing program management plans in support of engineering systems.   Functional Responsibility: Performs systems analysis/design, implementation and integration using database systems, and applies comprehensive knowledge of engineering management.   Minimum Education: Bachelor’s or Associate’s Degree, or high school diploma with four years experience without a degree.

raw_data.title: Technical Editor
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  Two years experience proofreading letters and technical reports; editing letters and documents; research of applicable specifications to determine conformity; excellent command of the English language. Functional Responsibility:  Performs editing, proofreading of technical reports, documents and letters; recommends changes and corrections. Minimum Education:  High School diploma or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Technical Manager
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  Eight years directly related work experience in the specialized area of responsibility to include formal assignment in a managerial capacity. Functional Responsibility:  Coordinates schedules and tasks, provides advice, guidance, and training to subordinates and recommends/determines personnel actions for the organization.  Responsible for project planning, execution, and performance. Minimum Education:  Bachelor’s Degree or four years of college level education, training, and/or technical experience that furnished a thorough knowledge in the specialized area of responsibility.

raw_data.title: Typist
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: One year working on typing and word processing equipment; preparation of documents and technical data, and a working knowledge of office equipment and procedures.   Functional Responsibility: Under routine supervision, performs typing and word processing of correspondence and technical data and reports. Minimum Education: High School diploma or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Welder/Burner/Brazier
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Two years technical experience in welding processes and theory.  Functional Responsibility: Performs welding and burning and brazing in accordance with approved guidelines and procedures. Minimum Education: High School or vocational school diploma, or equivalent.
